<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#000040">Originally posted by Thrud Gutchewer on 01-26-2000 11:28 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">There is no way you can fix a full melee class. Spells in every RPG i have ever played are god when you reach higher lv. Most of you have to admit it that have played RPG. In UO online every one became a warrior mage.. In D&D 50th lv casters could waste most foes if they could get it off in a shot. In Pallidium the same goes... spells are just God like in any sword and sorcery RPG after a certain lv.. 

Warriors (or warrior classes)only advatage was (in most) they get more out of attributes.

Read you D&D amnual and check The stats..
Str- only class that can get high str and use the bonus
Dex-Get the extra bonuses to AC and to hit with bows
Constitution- extra hp from higher stat

These are to name the few.. They also got great hp, Protection versus what ever and way better AC then most (less hits= less damage) Or they had a built in toughness to take less damage from hits or have less effect from such a hit..Such as being stunned a caster class had no chance but a warrior laughed.. Stats go down cuse you are low on hp or from a forced march. Not a warrior there ready for days more of a march or dont feel the pain as fast..They know at a later lv how to control there fury and when to use it. So when the time comes to go nuts they do. Warrior A hits  gob A with his sword for X amount of damage. He grabs Gob B in other hand throws him into wall. He then flips around rips off GOB C's arms and beats him with them..

Untill A warrior can Do all this (maybe even after) We will never be as good as people want us to be In there eyes.. Plain and simple warriors rely on equipment yes But also on there stats. Make stats more effective in the game for us and i think youll see alot of happy warriors.

Sorry so long. I had to say it to blow off steam or cuse where slow at work    :). It would be longer cuse i would tell you what i think they should do but i think you have read enough of those posts    :)

Thanks for reading
Thrud
Sol Ro

